cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with computational geometry and combinatorial optimization problems related to line segments and arrangements. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The use of fixed parameter tractability in the paper suggests that it could belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper also discusses the linear time algorithm, which suggests that it could belong to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
